title: How to Make Money Growing and Selling Vegetable Starts

steps.headline: Go to your local garden store and pick up some packs of vegetable seeds.
steps.description: Get the seeds from the most sold (and highest quality) vegetables.

steps.headline: If you have a greenhouse, start growing them.
steps.description: If not, you will need to start your seeds indoors. Or build a small cold frame.

steps.headline: Get your soil ready and sprinkle seeds out in a row.
steps.description: Slightly cover your vegetable seed with a little bit of dirt.

steps.headline: Once the seeds germinate.
steps.description: They will grow fast. Real fast. After they get about 4-6 leaves, transplant them into 4" pots to be sold. Time to start the next set. Just set the new seed right where the first set was growing.

steps.headline: Provide bottom heat.
steps.description: Keeping the soil warm will increase growth rates. Grow larger stronger root systems and beautiful plants. Put a little tent over the top of the seeds for better germination rates. Provide some sun, but not full sun.

steps.headline: Keep it organic, as much as possible, because that's what sells.
steps.description: With bottom heat, you can have these plants ready to sell in about a month and a half. Now sell these little beauties cheaper than the local stores, and sell out. Plant the leftovers in your own garden.

steps.headline: After selling the first few plants, you will make your money back and the rest is profit.
Offer organic vegetables starts in your local classified ads.
steps.description: Organic veggie starts. You can make a tidy little profit doing this. You figure if you have 300 plants for sale at $2 to $3 a piece.

steps.headline: Sell at a local farmers' market.
steps.description: Or at your local Mom and Pop shops. Or restaurants or even large grocery stores. Many people want to buy the plants.

If not, you will need to start your seeds indoors. Or build a small cold frame. Get your soil ready and sprinkle seeds out in a row. Slightly cover your vegetable seed with a little bit of dirt.
